<h2 id="1-import-request-module">1. Import Request Module</h2>
<p>To ensure if requests module is avaible in our systems.<br /></p>

<p><strong>But, usually python is have requests module by default, so we can just import the module without install anything</strong></p>
<div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="o">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">requests</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="2-get-request">2. GET request</h2>
<p>To get data from somewhere</p>
<div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="o">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">requests</span>
<span class="o">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="n">request_result</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">requests</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">'http://YOUR_TARGET'</span><span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Then, to change <strong>requests</strong> object result, we can use several function in requests module, in this example we will change request result object to <a href="https://www.json.org/json-en.html">JSON</a></p>

<div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="o">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="n">request_json_result</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">request_result</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">json</span><span class="p">()</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
